This paper deals with the formal modeling of trust in the context of belief revision, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of state partitions and pseudometrics, which are concepts that are relevant to cryptography and security (cs.CR) and social networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper deals with the processing of multiple reports, which is a problem that is often studied in the context of distributed systems and algorithms (cs.DS).
